uint32_t detObjOutMaxSize
 This field dimensions several other fields in this structure as referred in their descriptions. It is determined by the dpc/application based on balancing between maximum number of objects expected to be detected in the scene (this can depend on configuration like cfar thresholds, static clutter removal etc) and memory and MIPS limitations.
 
cmplx16ImRe_t * azimuthStaticHeatMap
 Pointer to range-azimuth static heat map, this is a 2D FFT array in range direction (x[numRangeBins][numVirtualAntAzim]), at doppler index 0, sized to azimuthStaticHeatMapSize elements of type cplx16ImRe_t. Alignment should be DPU_AOAPROCHWA_AZIMUTH_STATIC_HEAT_MAP_BYTE_ALIGNMENT.
 
uint32_t azimuthStaticHeatMapSize
 Number of elements of azimuthStaticHeatMap, this should be numVirtualAntAzim * numRangeBins.
 
uint8_t * detObj2dAzimIdx
 Detected objects azimuth index for debugging, sized to detObjOutMaxSize elements.
 
float * detObjElevationAngle
 Detected object elevation angle for debugging, sized to detObjOutMaxSize elements, must be aligned to DPU_AOAPROCHWA_DET_OBJ_ELEVATION_ANGLE_BYTE_ALIGNMENT.
 
uint8_t * localScratchBuffer [DPU_AOAPROCHWA_NUM_LOCAL_SCRATCH_BUFFERS]
 Local scratch buffer.
 
uint32_t localScratchBufferSizeBytes
 Local scratch buffer size = numTxAntennas * DPU_AOAPROCHWA_NUM_ANGLE_BINS * sizeof(uint16_t). A convenient macro DPU_AOAPROCHWA_NUM_LOCAL_SCRATCH_BUFFER_SIZE_BYTES has been provided for calculating this size.
